			<ns0:name>eli...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112264824292994369940/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">When fixing ARM.td locally to restore the NEON feature for cortex-a8 which was earlier disabled by a LOCALMOD, we run into a couple of problems.

First of all, there's a validation step in pnacl/build.sh that checks the object files built by Pnacl for build attributes, and expects VFPv2 for ARM. Enabling NEON makes Pnacl emit VFPv3 instead. So pnacl/build.sh has to be updated accordingly.

A more serious problem is that LLVM actually emits NEON instructions for some of our Nacl tests, once the feature is enabled for cortex-a8. However, it doesn't know how to sandbox NEON instructions, so validation fails. So, LLVM needs to be taught how to sandbox NEON instructions.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-11-01T23:24:11.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-11-01T23:24:11.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 6 by eli...@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3124#c6" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3124/comments/full/6" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>